claims:
36. Method for producing at least one device according to claim 26, comprising the steps of
providing a Si-substrate, comprising at least one sensor,
a1) depositing/growing a first dielectric layer on both sides of the substrate, and
b) patterning the dielectric layer on a bottom side;
c) depositing a first polymer layer on the unpatterned Si-side of the dielectric layer;
d) patterning the first polymer layer using a lithography or electron beam machine;
e1) depositing a sacrificial layer on the first polymer layer;
e2) patterning the sacrificial layer using a lithography or electron beam machine; and etching the first polymer layer with plasma etching/dry etching;
f) depositing a second layer on the sacrificial layer;
g) dry etching the Silicon substrate at the bottom side, therewith providing openings for channels/chambers in Si;
h) (wet) etching of the first dielectric layer from the bottom side providing openings for channels/chambers; and
i) (wet) etching of the sacrificial layer thereby releasing channels/chambers.
